Prevent kwargs["tools"] = None from reaching the OpenAI Responses API.

`_responses_tools()` returns None when no tools are configured. The
SDK now rejects tools=None, so only set the tools key when we actually
have tools. Upstream already gates tool_choice / parallel_tool_calls
on response_tools — extend that gate to cover "tools" itself.

--- a/agent/transports/codex.py
+++ b/agent/transports/codex.py
@@ -99,11 +99,11 @@
             "input": _chat_messages_to_responses_input(
                 payload_messages,
                 is_xai_responses=is_xai_responses,
             ),
-            "tools": response_tools,
             "store": False,
         }
         if response_tools:
+            kwargs["tools"] = response_tools
             kwargs["tool_choice"] = "auto"
             kwargs["parallel_tool_calls"] = True
